import seaborn as sns
import statsmodels.api as sm
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='ignore')
    sns.lineplot(x='year', y='net_generation', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the trend of net electricity generation over the years?', wrap=True)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
```

import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='ignore')
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    sns.barplot(x='source', y='net_generation', data=data, estimator=sum, ci=None)
    plt.title('What is the proportion of electricity generated from each energy source?', wrap=True)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], errors='ignore')
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    sns.barplot(x='source', y='net_generation', data=data, estimator=lambda x: sum(x) / len(x), ci=None)
    plt.title('What is the average net electricity generation for each energy source?', wrap=True)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
```
